subject: Marathon Running
lead_paragraph: After two months of reviewing videos second by second, Honolulu Marathon Association officials are giving up on getting precise results from the race. Officials said nearly 2,000 finishers were left out of the results and less than 8 percent of the nearly 23,000 finishers were timed correctly.
